Large portions made to order. I usually order the lunch or dinner special Mongolian chicken. I don't like onions or peppers which is pretty much all there is to Mongolian chicken and they are willing to replace with another vegetable or no veggies at all and have never charged me extra. The portions given are very large and I easily always have some to take home. Very recommended.!!!

I ordered 6 jumbo chicken wings ahead and got there too quick for the order to be completed,  but I didn't mind the wait.The wings were every BITE worth it wings are the best, whenever I choose to eat fried chicken,  even better than Popeyes to me.  That was, all that I had ordered,  because I had already cooked the rest of my dinner. I have had their Vegetable and Shrimp Fried Rice too, at other times. Which were both good 😋

My go-to place for Chinese takeout. The workers are so friendly and we come here at least once a week for food AND drinks. Highly recommend their combination specials with a Thai milk tea. The woman who works the front counter is extremely kind and you can tell love goes into the drinks she makes.

We ordered the general tsao’s, vegetable lo mein, pot stickers, and egg rolls.! Delivery was on point. Portions were huge and delicious.!The egg rolls and pot stickers were larger sized compared to most places I’ve bought from! And the over all price WITH delivery and tip was significantly cheaper then other places. Much wow!! For people complaining about delivery, keep in mind #grubhub is a third party system so that’s not on them.

Certainly a place worth stopping by, the food is great and well prepared, the rates are affordable and it is regularly clean here. Fantastic work.

I like to go with friends to this place with my highest recommendations. I visit this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The the cooking is delicious and the stuff is generous and cooperative. Whenever we go to this place we pass a splendid evening.  I recommend this place with pleasure.

I was a very loyal customer going at least every week or two. However, after last night, I'm done. I called ahead to order my food. Thought 15 minutes ahead would be enough so that I could just pay and leave. Instead i had to wait another 15 mintues in the restuarant. Over 30 minutes for a small meal is obsurd but the fact that they were not apologetic rubbed me wrong. A huge issue is that i paid for the dinner box but got the lunch box which is a lot smaller and $2 less and only offered before 3. I didnt realuze thus until I got home. I think this was done intentionally because when I tried to get the guy's attention for more soy sauce he ignored me for a while then seemed relieved when that was all I wanted. Food is decent but customer service is trash.

One of the best Chinese restaurants I've had  in years. And I haven't even been there yet, just delivery.  My mouth actually watered preparing a plate.  Their food is clean and awesome.  Love the Kung Pao Chicken and Veggie Spring rolls.  I have yet to have something here that wasn't completely delicious.  Spicy food fans, try this place!

The price is great, and they give you massive amounts of food! The food is pretty good. We ordered online and it took a little longer to get it than what we were told. Employees were very nice, though. Overall not too shabby.

Delicious, huge portions and affordable!  I submitted a huge catering order with them for an event of about 80 people. 80 people came to the event, went for seconds and thirds, all the staff were well fed, and we barely touched half of the food they sent. All of the dishes we ordered were delicious!! We had several guests come to us saying that they really enjoyed the food.  The staff are very professional, very helpful and accommodating. Because we inevitably had a lot of leftovers, we asked them to come back to our venue for take out boxes, and they delivered them promptly. All of my co-workers, including myself, are very much impressed by this business.

Really good, flavorful food that's reasonably priced, and the portions are generous! They have your food ready in a matter of only 15 minutes on average, which is awesome. Customer service is also great! Conveniently located by the Thorndale stop.
Food is inexpensive. I ordered the beef fried rice(simple right) and it tasted like old leftovers. It is conviently located but trust me, bypass this place and try a different restaurant.

Pretty decent food, and really reasonably priced. I usually get the dinner special and a small soup for around $11. The portions are huge, I'll get a dinner and lunch and maybe even a small snack from one special. Pictured is the sesame chicken w chicken fried rice & an egg-roll. Small Wonton soup. Not a good place to dine in, but takeout is quick and easy!

Food is very good and not expensive. It's a nice place to have nearby in the neighborhood if you're looking for a quick meal. I love their chicken lo mein! I usually have enough leftover to last a couple meals.

Don't get me wrong, it's a counter service, low price Chinese place, so there are some issues.  The food doesn't appear to be one of them.  Items taste fresh and made to order.  Staff is friendly.  I go monthly for lunch.

This place is actually decent, contrary to most reviews. There are some dishes that seem to be very similar, and it appears that they use a similar sauce, just adjusted slightly for a different dish. The orange chicken dish is value for money, but don't order the prawns (they were terribly expensive)...
I got two orders of fried rice one tasted like burnt rice the other one had no flavor
Got a plate of "cashew chicken" that tasted like piss. You can feel the despair radiating from this place as soon as you walk in. Avoid at all costs.
The portion size is huge. Definitely a good place to snag food.

This restaurant was decent under the old management but it was sold and its just not very good anymore.   I watched as a customer noted his order was incomplete and a second received the wrong thing.   Forgivable if they were busy not so much when you have a total of four customers.   I enjoyed going there when they had the nice girls and young man working.   Now its just joyless and the food taste and quality has fallen.   I would avoid going here and its a shame because I used to like it.

The worst place you can order from. DO NOT make the same mistake I did. Mistake after mistake which they never cared to fix by sending the correct order or god forbid a free egg roll as an apology. Third time was the charm when they as usual added peanuts when asked not to and gave fried rice instead of steamed rice (this WILL happen EVERY time GUARANTEED) and I called them and started to eat the food anyway cause they never come back. But they did AND TOOK THE LEFTOVERS AND SAID THEY WILL JUST ADD FOOD TO IT AND RESELL THE DISH I WAS EATING. IF YOU LIKE OTHER PEOPLES LEFTOVERS THIS IS THE PLACE FOR YOU! ENJOY!

Here's why I hated the food at Grand China:  -The "fried" wontons were balls of chicken wrapped vertically with wonton skins and left out for at least 2 hours, I couldn't chew through 50% of the wonton  -The orange chicken was ridiculously sweet with some kind of rehydrated chili powder on them  -The only bonus was that they were apart from grub hub.  Don't come here.
Meh. I would give the restaurant another try because my SO liked it and it's cheap, but the chow mein was nothing I want to eat again.

Worst Chinese food experience I've ever had. I ordered the same dish on three different occasions, and every time I got something completely different. When I called the restaurant to tell them that I was not satisfied with the dish, they told me that maybe I forgot what it tastes like, and that they were "Busy with a customer" and hung up on me! There's too many goddamn Chinese food restaurants in Chicago to have to put up with this terrible service! Please do not waste your money

Horrible experience!!! We ordered from here primarily for the Bubble Tea(one of our favorite things) and talk about MAJOR disappointment! First, the food was late. We ordered delivery and we ordered through Grub Hub and our estimated time was over an hour..so we waited knowing it was a Friday night we gave them the benefit of the doubt. well, we waited and waited and waited some more...FINALLY our food shows up, late but what ever that was the least of my worries at the time. The first thing we unpacked was what was supposed to be our bubble tea because it is an iced drink. Well, the drinks were spilled everywhere it didn't even look like there was effort put into keeping our drinks contained and then THEY WERE HOT. It was NOT what we ordered! So we called to ask if the ordered could be fixed and talk about horrible customer service! The lady who answered the phone did nothing but get upset with us and argue, completely wasted phone call! So then we get to our food, we had ordered Orange Chicken, General Tso Chicken, and Kung Pao Chicken...and keep in mind we all can take a little bit of heat with no problem BUT this stuff was all so spicy that it wasn't tolerable..we couldn't even enjoy our food after all that nonsense, really? NEVER ORDERING FROM HERE AGAIN
great prices and portions
As far as the basics, the food is actually better than you average take-out place. Plus they offer some more authentic offerings for your advanced Chinese food eaters.

Probably worst Chinese I've had in a while. I agree with the guy who wrotethe review about the white sauce, it was on everything I've ever ordered from there. The first time I went, I thought it as a fluke but when it happened again I didn't go back. The kitchen moves super slow if they're busy, waited 50 minutes for shrimp lo mein and egg rolls. Egg rolls were burnt, shrimp tasted like metal. Ended up having to make something when I got home.
Order from here often.  Service and delivery is very nice. Food is good and warm on delivery.  The folks who run it are really nice people and I like the food.

Got Mongolian Beef Dinner for pick up. Walking home, the package of food was very heavy and when I got home the styrafoam container was full to the brim of delicious fried rice and Mongolian beef. Good food, very convenient.
